s sentenced to 3 years in prison for illegally selling state gifts. Police arrested him after a court sentenced him to three years. Imran Khan's lawyer says the former prime minister was arrested by police. Khan was arrested in Pakistan's capital, Islamabad, on suspicion of illegally selling gifts.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 09:10:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">NBC News</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/pakistan-imran-khan-arrested-court-lahore-sentence-selling-state-gifts-rcna98302" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/california-homeless-shelter-sweeping-paused-sacramento" target="_blank">California judge pauses sweeping of homeless encampments amid heatwave</a></h2><div class="description"> Federal judge in California has placed temporary ban on sweeps of homeless encampments. Order was issued against the city of Sacramento on 3 August, after advocates called out the municipality for violating its own order by sweeping an encampment during a time of excessive heat, which is anything over 90F.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 00:29:59 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/california-homeless-shelter-sweeping-paused-sacramento" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/san-diego-teens-arrested-killing-woman-pellet-gun" target="_blank">San Diego teens arrested for killing unhoused woman known as ‘Granny Annie’</a></h2><div class="description"> Annette Pershal, 68, was found on the street unconscious on 8 May and taken to the hospital. Doctors discovered she’d been shot multiple times with a pellet gun. She died several days later and her death was ruled a homicide. Pershal had lived on the streets for years and was known to locals as ‘Granny Annie’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 00:29:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/san-diego-teens-arrested-killing-woman-pellet-gun" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/donald-trump-rape-language-e-jean-carroll" target="_blank">Judge says E Jean Carroll allegation Trump raped her is ‘substantially true’ in court dismissal</a></h2><div class="description"> Ex-president claimed that writer defamed him when saying he raped her. But judge said term is commonly ‘used and understood’ in context. Trump lost his counterclaim for defamation against E Jean Carroll, the writer against whom he was found liable for sexual abuse and defamation and fined $5m.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:33:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/donald-trump-rape-language-e-jean-carroll" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/new-york-city-plans-house-migrants-randalls-island" target="_blank">New York City plans to house migrants on an island in the East River</a></h2><div class="description"> Mayor Eric Adams plans to house as many as 2,000 adults seeking asylum, in tent city where center opened and then closed last year. The state will reimburse the city for the cost of operating a tent city for adult migrants on Randalls Island, Adams said. The center was set up last year and then taken down weeks later.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:31:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/new-york-city-plans-house-migrants-randalls-island" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/five-hundred-pound-bear-hank-tank-caught" target="_blank">Five-hundred-pound bear ‘Hank the Tank’ caught after home break-ins in Tahoe area</a></h2><div class="description"> Bear was initially misgendered as a male and matched by DNA to more than 21 home break-ins and other instances of property damage in the Lake Tahoe region since 2022. She was “safely immobilized” by tranquilizer dart and apprehended Friday morning. She will now be moved to a sanctuary in southern Colorado.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:45:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/five-hundred-pound-bear-hank-tank-caught" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/tou-thao-minneapolis-police-officer-sentenced-george-floyd-murder" target="_blank">Ex-officer sentenced to nearly five years for role in George Floyd’s murder</a></h2><div class="description"> Tou Thao held crowds back as other officers restrained George Floyd. He was found guilty of aiding and abetting second-degree manslaughter by a jury in May. He had claimed that he merely served as a ‘human traffic cone’ during the deadly encounter. He has denied any role in Floyd’s death.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 18:24:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/tou-thao-minneapolis-police-officer-sentenced-george-floyd-murder" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-job-of-a-lifetime-why-i-quit" target="_blank">Harry Potter and the Cursed Child was the job of a lifetime, and I walked away from it | Gillian Cosgriff</a></h2><div class="description"> There's an untouchability about something that's supposed to be wondrous that means we shy away from hearing about the full spectrum of the experience. I was cast as Moaning Myrtle in 2018 and took over the role of Delphi in 2020. I stayed with the show for just over three years, performing in Melbourne’s beautiful Princess theatre.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:00:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-job-of-a-lifetime-why-i-quit" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/i-am-50-today-and-i-no-longer-care-what-anyone-thinks-about-my-age" target="_blank">I am 50 today – and I no longer care what anyone thinks about my age</a></h2><div class="description"> Ever since I was a teenager, people have thought I am much older than I actually am. When I was 14, someone thought I was my nine-year-old sister’s mum. In purely practical terms, imagining me having had her at, say, 14, that would put me at nine years over my actual age.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:21:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/i-am-50-today-and-i-no-longer-care-what-anyone-thinks-about-my-age" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/will-donald-trump-be-jailed-before-trial" target="_blank">Will Donald Trump be jailed before his trial? | Robert Reich</a></h2><div class="description"> The former president continues to threaten witnesses despite warnings not to violate conditions of release. Judge Moxila A Upadhyaya warned him that he could be taken into custody if he violated the conditions of his release, including attempting to influence jurors or intimidate future witnesses. She called him ‘Mr Trump’ rather than President Trump – thereby emphasizing that he was being treated as any criminal defendant would be treated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 14:30:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/will-donald-trump-be-jailed-before-trial" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/tinder-dating-app-subscription-long-term-relationship-love" target="_blank">Tinder wants to sell a $500-a-month subscription. Can they justify that? | Nancy Jo Sales</a></h2><div class="description"> Tinder has announced it is moving ahead with plans to launch a new “high-end” membership for as much as $500 a month. Tinder Vault will provide an “even more fun experience” and “quality matches” for “exclusive” users.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:42:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/tinder-dating-app-subscription-long-term-relationship-love" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/email-dread-pigeons-message-inbox" target="_blank">Email makes my fingers tingle and my stomach drop with dread. Can’t we go back to pigeons? | Emma Beddington</a></h2><div class="description"> Recent research on the ‘best time to send an email has highlighted for me how awful email is all the time. As a new French citizen, perhaps I should insist on my legal right to disconnect out of hours. Ideally, I’d like no work-related emails before 10am, between midday and 2pm, after 6pm.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/email-dread-pigeons-message-inbox" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/a-giant-oarfish-the-mirrored-harbinger-of-earthquakes" target="_blank">A giant oarfish: the mirrored harbinger of earthquakes | Helen Sullivan</a></h2><div class="description"> Giant oarfish is an eight-metre long ribbon of silver, tapered at its tail and on its head wearing a permanently stunned face. Oarfish swim vertically, moving up and down and side to side like a cursor. They’re known as ‘messengers from the sea god’s palace’ in Japan.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 15:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/a-giant-oarfish-the-mirrored-harbinger-of-earthquakes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/07/anderson-and-ramirez-banned-for-fight-that-sparked-white-sox-guardians-brawl" target="_blank">Anderson and Ramírez banned for fight that sparked White Sox-Guardians brawl</a></h2><div class="description"> Tim Anderson suspended for six games, José Ramírez for three games by Major League Baseball. Anderson sparked a brawl between the White Sox and Guardians on Saturday night. Both players are appealing against their penalties. Anderson and Ramirez are also fined an undisclosed amount by the league.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:46:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/07/anderson-and-ramirez-banned-for-fight-that-sparked-white-sox-guardians-brawl" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-soccer-penalty-retirement-world-cup" target="_blank">The Megan Myth: what critics and fans get wrong about Rapinoe</a></h2><div class="description"> World Cup champion's career on the sporting stage is drawing to a close. Many people who would call themselves patriotic delighted, with no apparent awareness of irony, in an American defeat. But in a country still in the throes of the Great Polarization, many people would be delighted with the defeat.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 17:30:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-soccer-penalty-retirement-world-cup" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href