dia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/introduction-of-chip-enabled-e-passports-will-strengthen-security-of-travel-documents-jaishankar-3110064.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/karnataka-seeks-isro-s-tech-support-to-improve-efficiency-of-road-transport-corps-3080077.html" target="_blank">Karnataka seeks ISRO's tech support to improve efficiency of road transport corps</a></h2><div class="description"> Karnataka government has sought the help of ISRO on improving the efficiency of road transport corporations in the state. Deputy Chief Minister Laxman Savadi, who is also the Minister in-charge of Transport Department, said the government is looking to use ISRO's technology to improve road transport efficiency.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 29 Apr 2020 17:46:50 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/karnataka-seeks-isro-s-tech-support-to-improve-efficiency-of-road-transport-corps-3080077.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/cricket/kohli-was-destined-for-greatness-says-pietersen-3063154.html" target="_blank">Kohli was destined for greatness, says Pietersen</a></h2><div class="description"> Kevin Pietersen was one of the most destructive batsman in world cricket. The flamboyant batsman was one the most powerful batsman of all time. It was no wonder Pietersen sent the bowlers on a leather hunt for the bowler. The former England batsman is one of cricket's most destructive cricketers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 08 Apr 2020 10:31:29 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/cricket/kohli-was-destined-for-greatness-says-pietersen-3063154.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/football/bundesliga-game-week-7-roundup-results-2235794.html" target="_blank">Bundesliga game week 7: Roundup and results</a></h2><div class="description"> Ten-men Frankfurt held to a 2-2 draw against Bayern Munich. Cologne defeated Ingolstadt 2-1 to move at the second spot in the seventh round matches of the German Bundesliga. The German giants were unable to defend their two-goal lead in the Bundesliga.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 17 Oct 2016 14:27:44 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/football/bundesliga-game-week-7-roundup-results-2235794.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/cricket/rohit-sharma-plays-first-odi-at-wankhede-stadium-1909106.html" target="_blank">Rohit makes me laugh without even trying, says fiancee Ritika Sajdeh</a></h2><div class="description"> Rohit Sharma made his ODI debut in the year 2007 but it took him almost 8 years to play his first limited overs match in his own backyard, at Wankhede Stadium, Mumbai. Rohit played his first ODI ODI match at the stadium since 2007.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 25 Oct 2015 16:57:59 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/cricket/rohit-sharma-plays-first-odi-at-wankhede-stadium-1909106.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/full-list-leander-paes-grand-slam-trophies-1867243.html" target="_blank">Full list of Leander Paes' Grand Slam trophies</a></h2><div class="description"> Leander Paes won the US Open mixed doubles title with Martina Hingis on Saturday. The 42-year-old now has 17 Grand Slam titles in his career. Paes now has won 17 of the Grand Slams, including four titles in singles singles.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Sep 2015 15:39:30 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/sports/full-list-leander-paes-grand-slam-trophies-1867243.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2013/03/15/uefa-champions-league-2012-13-round-of-16-results-1172515.html" target="_blank">UEFA Champions League 2012-13 Round of 16 Results</a></h2><div class="description"> Arsenal crashed out of the Champions League round of 16 for the third consecutive year. Arsenal beat Bayern Munich 2-0 in the second leg at the Emirates. The Gunners went down 3-1 in the first-leg but managed to win the second-leg 2-1.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 15 Mar 2013 17:57:19 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2013/03/15/uefa-champions-league-2012-13-round-of-16-results-1172515.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2011/02/26/sharathshamini-clinch-tt-mixed-doublesgold-aid0126.html" target="_blank">TT mixed doubles: Sharath-Shamini bags gold</a></h2><div class="description"> Achanta Sharath Kamal clinched the mixed doubles title with national champion Kumaresan Shamini. He stormed into the men's singles summit clash in Ranchi, India, on Friday, Feb 25. He is aiming to win another gold after storming into the final of the tournament at the Rio de Janeiro Games.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 09 Dec 2011 06:38:24 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2011/02/26/sharathshamini-clinch-tt-mixed-doublesgold-aid0126.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2011/02/26/punefc-take-on-in-form-vivakerala-aid0126.html" target="_blank">I-League: Pune FC faces in-form Viva Kerala</a></h2><div class="description"> Pune FC will need to be cautious of an in-form Viva Kerala if they are to extend their three-match unbeaten streak in the I-League. Viva's 7-1 home win over Air India is the biggest margin of victory in the league.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 09 Dec 2011 06:38:23 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2011/02/26/punefc-take-on-in-form-vivakerala-aid0126.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/william-friedkin-director-exorcist-french-connection-dies" target="_blank">William Friedkin created unforgettable horror and pleasure with equal brilliance</a></h2><div class="description"> The 87-year-old director leaves behind a thrilling, high-wire career mastering different genres in films such as The Exorcist, The French Connection and Cruising. He was a film-maker who could offer films with the thrillingly intravenous excitement of hard drugs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:58:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/william-friedkin-director-exorcist-french-connection-dies" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/compassionate-spy-documentary-ted-hall" target="_blank">‘What people accused Oppenheimer of doing’: the untold story of spy Ted Hall</a></h2><div class="description"> In Steve James’s documentary, A Compassionate Spy, a lesser-known figure from the Manhattan Project is given the spotlight. In a pivotal scene set during post-test celebrations, J Robert Oppenheimer, the theoretical physicist played by Cillian Murphy, stokes flames of triumphalism while seeing the ashes of future destruction.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 18:06:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/compassionate-spy-documentary-ted-hall" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/the-rooster-review-film-hugo-weaving-phoenix-raei-mark-leonard-winter" target="_blank">The Rooster review – Hugo Weaving kicks this study of masculinity into gear</a></h2><div class="description"> Actor turned film-maker Mark Leonard Winter’s directorial debut, The Rooster, is a bumpy outdoorsy drama about two broken men – a cop and a hermit – connecting and potentially healing through the deployment of pensive stares and introspective dialogue. The film's core dynamic works in contrasts, pairing Phoenix Raei's sullen cop Dan with a violently loud recluse.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/the-rooster-review-film-hugo-weaving-phoenix-raei-mark-leonard-winter" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/movie-theater-fights-cellphones-bad-behavior" target="_blank">Chaos in the aisles: has cinema etiquette reached an all-time low?</a></h2><div class="description"> A summer box office boom, thanks to Barbenheimer, has led to multiple stories of bad behaviour at the movies, from fights to phone usage. Anything that prolongs the life of cinema deserves to be celebrated, but newcomers have clearly forgotten how cinemas are supposed to work. The last few weeks have seen a rash of headlines about a number of regrettable blow-ups.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:20:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/movie-theater-fights-cellphones-bad-behavior" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/jess-search-obituary" target="_blank">Jess Search obituary</a></h2><div class="description"> Jess Search sought to harness the power of non-fiction storytelling to bring about change on issues such as the climate crisis and defending democracy. The many dozens of films she funded, advised, mentored, distributed, produced or executive produced include Citizenfour, Virunga and Knock Down the House.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:38:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/jess-search-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/the-communion-girl-review-victor-garcia-spanish-horror" target="_blank">The Communion Girl review – teens spooked by holy terror in creepy-doll horror</a></h2><div class="description"> Director Víctor García draws on convincing period setting to nourish his scare story. Stifling religious and social conformity of a small Spanish town is source of the shocks. The sense of claustrophobic entrapment in the milieu is undermined by a cop-out open ending.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/the-communion-girl-review-victor-garcia-spanish-horror" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/promising-young-woman-follow-up-london-film-festival-emerald-fennell" target="_blank">Promising Young Woman follow-up Saltburn given opening slot at London film festival</a></h2><div class="description"> Emerald Fennell’s film, starring Barry Keoghan, Jacob Elordi and Rosamund Pike, is ‘a tale of privilege and desire’ following a young student at Oxford. It has been selected as the opening film for the 2023 edition of the London film festival.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 11:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/promising-young-woman-follow-up-london-film-festival-emerald-fennell" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/kuwait-bans-hit-australian-horror-film-talk-to-me-over-casting-of-trans-actor-zoe-terakes" target="_blank">Kuwait bans hit Australian horror film Talk to Me over casting of trans actor Zoe Terakes</a></h2><div class="description"> Australian actor Zoe Terakes, who plays a character whose gender is never mentioned in the film, called the decision ‘targeted and dehumanising’ Terakes is also the first trans actor to be cast in a Marvel TV series, with a role in the upcoming superhero show Ironheart.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 10:06:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/kuwait-bans-hit-australian-horror-film-talk-to-me-over-casting-of-trans-actor-zoe-terakes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/barbie-movie-tops-1bn-in-global-box-office-ticket-sales-breaking-record-for-female-directors" target="_blank">Barbie movie tops $1bn in global box office ticket sales, breaking record for female directors</a></h2><div class="description"> Barbie has broken the US$1bn mark since its debut more than two weeks ago. The movie took in $459m from North American theatres and another $572.1m overseas over the weekend. Barbie is now the biggest film to be directed by one woman, with director Greta Gerwig supplanting Patty Jenkins.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 01:01:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/barbie-movie-tops-1bn-in-global-box-office-ticket-sales-breaking-record-for-female-directors" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/06/jamie-foxx-apologizes-instagram-post-antisemitism" target="_blank">Jamie Foxx apologizes after Instagram post draws accusations of antisemitism</a></h2><div class="description"> Actor Jamie Foxx apologizes to Jewish community for post on Instagram. Post read: “They killed this dude name Jesus … what do you think they’ll do to you???! #fakefriends #fakelove” But the 55-year-old entertainer deleted the post after fellow users asserted that it echoed belief that Jewish people all together as one crucified and killed Jesus Christ.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 13:56:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/06/jamie-foxx-apologizes-instagram-post-antisemitism" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One review – Tom Cruise does it better</a></h2><div class="description"> Seven films in and nothing about M:I, from the star’s incredible stunt skills to the silly-serious tone, is showing any sign of slowing down. Already, the keynote stunt has become a legend: the one on the poster, the one he reportedly did – for real – six times in one day before he was satisfied. The seventh in the Mission: Impossible action franchise with Cruise starring as Ethan Hunt.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 10:45:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">The Deepest Breath review – stunning Netflix documentary on freediving</a></h2><div class="description"> The Deepest Breath is a love story embedded in the world of free diving, the deadly extreme sport whose practitioners plunge toward the ocean floor, often wearing nothing but a wetsuit and nose plug. (Goggles are out of the question since the air pressure would cause blood vessels in the eyes to burst.)</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 10 Jul 2023 13:23:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Insidious: The Red Door review – shoddy horror sequel</a></h2><div class="description"> Patrick Wilson makes his directorial debut with a labored legacy sequel that should hopefully close the door on the long-running franchise. The unifying premise for hit factory Blumhouse’s reliable yet reliably uninteresting moneymaker dares viewers to wonder “what if there was a creepy thing that jumped out at you, then disappeared?”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Joy Ride review – slickly likable Asian-American comedy dwells on family and identity</a></h2><div class="description"> Laughs, high energy levels and some outrageous set pieces make this examination of the complex relationship with distant family a fun journey of self-discovery. Adele Lim, who worked on the script for Crazy Rich Asians, now makes her feature directing debut with this likable and brash Asian-American comedy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 06 Jul 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">The Out-Laws review – Pierce Brosnan can’t save limp Netflix comedy</a></h2><div class="description"> The ex-007 plays a criminal father-in-law in an Adam Sandler-ushered action comedy that misses every time. Adam DeVine, from the cult sitcom Workaholics, is a bundle of nice-guy nerves, a cartoon beta. The true Happy Madison stinkers are the ones even he wouldn’t headline.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:10:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny review - Harrison Ford cracks the whip in taut sequel</a></h2><div class="description"> Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny is the fifth Indiana Jones film in which the legendary archaeologist and whip-cracking adventurer is back for another go-around. Harrison Ford, now 80 years young, carries off with humour and style and still nailing that reluctant crooked smile.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 16:44:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">No Hard Feelings review – Jennifer Lawrence comedy plays sex work for laughs</a></h2><div class="description"> Jennifer Lawrence plays Maddie, a woman in her early 30s who has been unlucky in love. She still lives in her childhood home, all alone since the death of her mother. She scratches a living as an Uber driver, but her car gets repossessed for non-payment of Montauk’s exorbitant property taxes on a house.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 12:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Elemental review – fire and water fall in love in multicoloured, unworldly Pixar fable</a></h2><div class="description"> Decent family entertainment set in the city of four elements, with a message of acceptance in bricks of colour and concepts as if originated via algorithm. It is also a star-crossed love story based on that most traditional of American themes: melting-pot diversity in the big city.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 19 Jun 2023 12:00:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Fast X review – stupidly entertaining sequel offers more of the same</a></h2><div class="description"> The Fast & Furious franchise reached the ideal level of sublime ridiculousness with Fast Five. The films that followed have tried nobly to top the simple, lizard-brain pleasure of this moment. Fast X seems to recognize Fast Five as the top of the franchise bell curve, because it starts there, by retconning a super-villain.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 17 May 2023 16:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">White Men Can’t Jump review – comedy remake fumbles the shot</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinqua Walls and Jack Harlow fail to recall the magic of the 1992 hit in a shallow and mostly unfunny nostalgia play. Vince Staples and Myles Bullock are the best couple on screen. Teyana Taylor brings her true life experience as an NBA wife to the part of Kamal’s partner, Imani.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 18 May 2023 13:37:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">The Mother review – Jennifer Lopez goes kick-ass in abject kidnap thriller</a></h2><div class="description"> There's some real ChatGPT film-making here in this abjectly formulaic and inert Netflix thriller from director Niki Caro. Lopez plays an ex-special forces parent aiming to rescues her kid from the bad guys. One villain (Gael García Bernal) disappears from the plot about halfway in, presumably left on cutting-room floor.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 12 May 2023 01:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Why is Hollywood on strike (and why Succession’s Brian Cox is joining them)? - podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Production on Hollywood films and TV shows has ground to a halt because of the Sag-Aftra strike. Michael Safi speaks to Lois Beckett, a senior reporter with Guardian US, and Brian Cox, who played media boss Logan Roy in the TV series Succession, on why writers and actors can no longer make a living.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 15:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Why do Republicans hate the Barbie movie? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Conservatives have slated Barbie for being, among other things, too ‘woke’, anti-men and even Chinese propaganda. Is the outrage real or is it just another example of politics employing a culture war to rally the base? Jonathan Freedland and Amanda Marcotte try to figure it out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: actor Simon Pegg, Marina Hyde on the benevolent Lord Lebedev, and the truth about inflammation</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Pegg on joining the A-list elite and embracing home life in Blighty. Marina Hyde implores us to ignore Lord Lebedev's links to the KGB and just focus on his successes. Joel Snape reveals all you need to know about 2023’s hottest health topic: inflammation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 01 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Our critics’ guide to a summer of music, movies and culture - podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Guardian culture writers Alex Needham, Ellen E Jones and Michael Cragg take Nosheen Iqbal on a guided tour of the summer. They pick their picks of the best of this summer in arts and culture from the Guardian's top picks of arts and literature.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 02:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: Little Mermaid star Halle Bailey, Marina Hyde on the This Morning ‘rift’, and the bereaved sex taboo</a></h2><div class="description"> Marina Hyde talks about Holly Willoughby and Philip Schofield's alleged rift. Halle Bailey talks about overcoming self-doubt and her soulmate sister Chlöe. Author Kat Lister explores the stigma of grieving partners’ sexuality and the loss of sexual intimacy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/barbies-muddled-feminist-fantasy-still-bows-to-the-patriarchy" target="_blank">Barbie’s muddled feminist fantasy still bows to the patriarchy</a></h2><div class="description"> Greta Gerwig’s fantasy comedy Barbie is ushering womankind on to the path to sisterly empowerment. Critic Toby Young has accused it of “unapologetic misandry” while Critical Drinker considered it “114 minutes of spiteful, bitter, mean-spirited, borderline unhinged hatred of men”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 12:18:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/barbies-muddled-feminist-fantasy-still-bows-to-the-patriarchy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">See no evil: why have baddies vanished from our cinema screens?</a></h2><div class="description"> Tom Cruise’s latest villain is in fact a sentient computer code. An uncomplicatedly bad villain used to feature in every action film worth its salt. But a more globalised industry has made the universally hated figure a tricky character to pull off. An action movie without a real villain? Hans Gruber would be spinning in his grave.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 15:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Watership Down has been upgraded to a PG. That won’t stop it terrifying children | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> The 1978 animated version of Watership Down has been upgraded from U to PG (Parental Guidance) It is a remarkable example of censoring authority becoming more puritanical over time. The overwhelming threat of violence is part of what has made Watership down so compelling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 14:38:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Has Barbie killed the indie director? Credible film-makers are shamelessly selling out | Caspar Salmon</a></h2><div class="description"> One-time indie cinema darling Greta Gerwig is now making money for a megabucks toy company that sells vacuous, hypersexualised dolls – and no one bats an eyelid. Sarah Polley was asked by Disney executives to remove a peace sign badge she was wearing. When she refused, Disney blacklisted her.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 10:42:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Latest Mission: Impossible shows the ‘silent Asian’ stereotype is alive and well</a></h2><div class="description"> Pom Klementieff’s supporting role as Paris, a savage assassin, is transformed into the tired stereotype of the silent Asian. Paris is largely mute throughout the film, flying in the face of more enlightened recent film roles. The French actor, who is half Korean, barely utters a word throughout the whole thing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 10:10:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Jane Birkin: a tremendous screen presence with a gift for creative collaboration | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> Birkin made a sensational impact in Blow-Up, and went on to become a classy performer for a number of major French directors – notably Godard and Agnès Varda. She was a performer with that interesting distinction of being Anglo-French, which somehow added to her unlocatable quality: she was quite at home with both languages.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 16 Jul 2023 17:22:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">I did my PhD in Hollywood action films – here’s why Mission: Impossible is the best | Clem Bastow</a></h2><div class="description"> The series has come to be characterised largely by Tom Cruise's spectacular stunts. But what sets them apart are Ethan Hunt’s very human qualities. The Mission: Impossible films are perhaps the key-est of my key works – for no other Hollywood franchise does action, or emotion, better.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 23:29:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Julian Sands: a hypnotically exotic actor full of style and extravagance</a></h2><div class="description"> After the smash hit of A Room With a View, Sands’ idiosyncrasies were hard to contain in mainstream movies, but in the right roles he was mesmerising. He delivered lines at about 60 to 70% of the speed at which other actors spoke. These were mannerisms that became more pronounced and sometimes baffling as he got older.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 21:30:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Academy, take action: why there should be an Oscar for best stunts</a></h2><div class="description"> The director of John Wick: Chapter 4 has revealed that he is in discussions with the Academy to officially recognise the power of action sequences. John Wick director John Wick is in talks with the academy to recognise action sequences in films. The Academy could be better recognised for commercial movies to be better recognised.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 15:15:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Fierce, sensual, cerebral: how Glenda Jackson brought class to film | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> The British actor was the epitome of countercultural chic in key 1970s films. It is just a shame she couldn't be persuaded to do more of them when her political career ended. The first Oscar was for playing Gudrun in Lawrence’s Women in Love.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 14:03:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Chris Hemsworth thinks Thor has become ‘too silly’ – if superheroes are turning on Marvel, is endgame nigh?</a></h2><div class="description"> Three Marvel stars have recently broken rank to reveal that their movies sort of suck. Hemsworth and Elizabeth Olsen are among the MCU stars to break rank and criticise their latest films. Marvel is in a slump, receiving its three lowest-ever Rotten Tomatoes scores in the last three years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 12:47:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/07/one-hit-wonder-barbie-world-with-aqua" target="_blank">‘Critics wanted us to be a one-hit-wonder’: back in Barbie world with Aqua</a></h2><div class="description"> Aqua's satirical take on Barbie pre-empted the hit film’s own subversion by 26 years. The Scandinavian pop group have noted some similarities with the film's subversion. Aqua's lead vocalist René Dif and keyboardist Søren Rasted looked at each other in elation and disbelief.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:41:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/07/one-hit-wonder-barbie-world-with-aqua" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/stardom-is-not-a-worthy-pursuit-julia-louis-dreyfus-on-sexism-ageing-and-fighting-fascism" target="_blank">‘Stardom is not a worthy pursuit’: Julia Louis-Dreyfus on sexism, ageing and fighting fascism</a></h2><div class="description"> Julia Louis-Dreyfus stars alongside Nicole Holofcener in new film You Hurt My Feelings. She discusses juggling parenting and working, dark days on SNL – and celebrating older women. The star of Seinfeld and Veep has barely put a foot wrong in her 40-year career.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/stardom-is-not-a-worthy-pursuit-julia-louis-dreyfus-on-sexism-ageing-and-fighting-fascism" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Victor Belmondo: ‘I wanted to be an actor – I never said to myself, yes, but that’s what Papi does too’</a></h2><div class="description"> Victor Belmondo, 29, has been quietly firing up his own acting career. He is unmistakably of the same lineage as his grandfather, Jean-Paul. At his grandfather’s funeral in 2021, he described the legendary nouvelle vague star as an ‘eternal sun’ Now beginning to light up the screen himself, he talks about trying to capture his predecessor's insouciance.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 14:03:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">‘The lowest I’ve ever been’: how playing Jar Jar Binks led to abuse, near death – and saving Baby Yoda</a></h2><div class="description"> Ahmed Best was overjoyed when cast as Jar Jar Binks - until threats of violence began. As a podcast tells his story, he talks about hate, making movie history and a glorious comeback in The Mandalorian. TED-produced podcast tells the story of the actor who played the character in Star Wars.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 12:13:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">How did Barbie do it? Warner’s head of marketing on creating a ‘pink movement’</a></h2><div class="description"> Greta Gerwig’s new Barbie movie broke box office records for the most commercially successful film by a female director. The film brought in more than $356m (£276m, A$527m) worldwide during its opening weekend and another $50m in tickets on Monday and Tuesday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 10:00:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">‘I was making a film about the trauma of an entire country’: director Alice Winocour on her movie about the 2015 Paris terror attacks</a></h2><div class="description"> After her brother was caught up in the Bataclan siege, Winocour wanted to address the events that had scarred France. Unlike the recent Jean Dujardin film November, it completely ignores religion and largely passes over the bloodshed. Instead, it joins films such as You Will Not Have My Hate and One Year, One Nigh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 07:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">‘It’s a nonstop dream’: the YouTuber twins behind Talk to Me, the scariest film of the year</a></h2><div class="description"> Adelaide brothers Danny and Michael Philippou, AKA RackaRacka, are in the middle of a whirlwind press tour for their horror debut, Talk to Me. The horror film unleashed a competitive bidding war at this year’s Sundance film festival and landed them a high seven-figure deal with A24.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:00:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Talk to Me review – an Evil Dead for the Snapchat generation</a></h2><div class="description"> Australian YouTuber twins Danny and Michael Philippou’s feature debut is an entertaining chiller that mixes shrieking horror and psychological nuance. Two years after the untimely death of her mother, 17-year-old Mia (Sophie Wilde) has retreated from her father, preferring to hang out at the home of her father.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/hypnotic-and-the-best-conspiracy-thrillers" target="_blank">Hypnotic and the best conspiracy thrillers</a></h2><div class="description"> The enjoyably daft sci-fi twister starring Ben Affleck is a good jumping-off point for classic intrigues ranging from The 39 Steps and JFK to Soylent Green and The Net. Audiences weren't persuaded - it tanked in cinemas – but I think it has the makings of classic midnight-marathon fodder.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 07:00:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/hypnotic-and-the-best-conspiracy-thrillers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/wonder-woman-3-gal-gadot-dc-multiverse-week-in-geek" target="_blank">Amazonian prime: why Wonder Woman 3 will be the star of the new-look DC multiverse</a></h2><div class="description"> There has been a cull at DC under studio boss James Gunn. Gal Gadot’s warrior princess stands tall, and her previously cancelled second sequel is back on. But news this week suggests this week that the previously cancelled sequel is set to go on this weekend.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 11:36:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/wonder-woman-3-gal-gadot-dc-multiverse-week-in-geek" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/sam-burgess-to-leave-souths-uk-super-league-head-coach-job/102701174" target="_blank">Sam Burgess to leave NRL's Souths for UK Super League head coach job</a></h2><div class="description"> South Sydney club legend Sam Burgess will leave his post as an assistant to head coach of English outfit Warrington. Burgess will become Warrington's new head coach at the end of the season. The club legend will join Warrington from South Sydney on a free transfer to Warrington next month.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 00:21:21 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/sam-burgess-to-leave-souths-uk-super-league-head-coach-job/102701174" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/emily-banks-wins-jewel-of-the-north-campdrafting-competition/102696700" target="_blank">Ringer wins Argyle diamond in revered campdraft that's 'a really big deal'</a></h2><div class="description"> Twenty-year-old Emily Banks wins the Kimberley's Jewel of the North campdrafting competition. The competition was held in Kimberley, WA and NT. Emily Banks is the first woman to win the competition in the state's history of the campdraft competition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 23:24:15 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/emily-banks-wins-jewel-of-the-north-campdrafting-competition/102696700" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/para-cyclist-petricola-claims-second-aussie-gold-world-titles/102700636" target="_blank">Para-cyclist Emily Petricola claims second Aussie gold at world cycling titles</a></h2><div class="description"> Emily Petricola doubles Australia's gold medal tally at the cycling worlds. Logan Martin has to settle for silver in the BMX freestyle freestyle. Australia's second gold medalist Logan Martin finishes with a silver medal in the freestyle event. Emily Peticola wins the gold medal for Australia at cycling worlds at the age of 16.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 21:35:26 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/para-cyclist-petricola-claims-second-aussie-gold-world-titles/102700636" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/women-world-cup-matildas-fans-pack-sydney-site-to-win-denmark/102700158" target="_blank">Cheers and jubilation: Matildas fans brought to their feet in Sydney as final whistle seals quarterfinals spot</a></h2><div class="description"> The excitement and positivity at the Darling Harbour fan site was palpable when Matildas' star player Sam Kerr came on the pitch in Australia's World Cup clash against Denmark. The excitement was palpable as the team's star player came on in the World Cup warm-up match.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:18:31 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/women-world-cup-matildas-fans-pack-sydney-site-to-win-denmark/102700158" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/five-quick-hits-women-world-cup-matildas-denmark-england-nigeria/102699730" target="_blank">Five quick hits: Sam Kerr returns to triumphant Matildas as her club teammate sees red for England</a></h2><div class="description"> Sam Kerr returns to action for England after being sent off against Nigeria. England beat Nigeria on penalties despite having young star sent off. Sam Kerr returned to playing action for the first time since returning from injury. England won 2-1 on penalties after losing 2-0 to Nigeria in the World Cup quarter-final.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 18:42:26 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/five-quick-hits-women-world-cup-matildas-denmark-england-nigeria/102699730" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/when-and-who-do-matildas-play-next-in-fifa-womens-world-cup/102696162" target="_blank">The Matildas have won their World Cup match against Denmark. What happens next?</a></h2><div class="description"> Sam Kerr-captained side play again in the FIFA Women's World Cup quarterfinals. Sam Kerr's side are currently in the process of reaching the quarterfinals of the tournament in Brazil. Kerr's team will be hoping to reach the last eight of the World Cup in Sao Paulo.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 18:41:56 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</s